  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (5a257ef 2023-04-13T00:15:44.043211000Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nanvil fork\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nI want to trace a txn on a specific height. Because `cast run` will run the txn on the latest block, I try to fork the chain to local on a history height.\r\n\r\nI run `anvil -f ${RPC_URL} --fork-block-number ${HEIGHT}` and it returned:\r\n```\r\nthread 'main' panicked at 'Failed to fetch network chain id: HTTPError(reqwest::Error { kind: Request, url: Url { scheme: \"https\", cannot_be_a_base: false, username: \"\", password: None, host: Some(Domain(\"https\")), port: None, path: \"//URL\", query: None, fragment: None }, source: hyper::Error(Connect, ConnectError(\"dns error\", Custom { kind: Uncategorized, error: \"failed to lookup address information: nodename nor servname provided, or not known\" })) })', /Users/runner/work/foundry/foundry/anvil/src/config.rs:798:58\r\nnote: run with `RUST_BACKTRACE=1` environment variable to display a backtrace\r\n[1]    3557 abort      anvil -f URL --fork-block-number 48738\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, I can fork that rpc with forge test script(`vm.createSelectFork(\"RPC\", 48738)`). So I think it's not the rpc's problem.\r\n\r\n",
